[http://www.flickr.com/photos/8468254@N02] The lamps in this photo cannot date before 1903 according to <a href="http://www.archiseek.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3968" rel="nofollow">Dublin Street Lighting</a>.
The original ornate electric lamps date from 1892. They were powered from a new station at Fleet St.
&quot;Sometime during 1903-1910 these relatively young electric lampposts were removed, probably due their antiquated technology. It's possible it happened in 1903 as this is the year the Fleet St station shut down in favour of the Pigeon House. &quot;

